Gapminder Plots

Explanation

Life expectancy has gone up throughout the years. Highest being from European countries and the lowest being from African countries. In the second plot European countries tend to have a lower population but higher Gdp. There are some Asian countries that have a low population but very high Gdp. From this, you can also see that Asian countries havethe higher populated areas

p1 = qplot(x = year, 
           y = lifeExp,
           color = continent, 
           ylab = "Life expectancy",
           xlab = "Year",
           data = gapminder,
           main = "Year in relation to Life expectancy")+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
p2 = qplot(x = pop, 
           y = gdpPercap,
           color = continent, 
           data = gapminder,
           xlab = "Population",
           ylab = "Gdp per Capita",
           main = "Population in relation to Gdp per Capita")

grid.arrange(p1,p2, ncol = 2)

rest = read.csv("http://vicpena.github.io/sta9750/spring19/nyc.csv")
rest$Location = rest$East

Food vs Price

fvp = ggplot(rest)+
  aes(x = Price, y = Food, color = Location)+
  geom_point()+
  theme_bw()+
  ggtitle("Food vs Price")+
  ylab("Food Quality")+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

fvp

Decor vs Service

dvs = fvp = ggplot(rest)+

Interfaith

inter = read.table("http://users.stat.ufl.edu/~winner/data/interfaith.dat")
colnames(inter) = c("ses","religion","gender","interfaith","count")
inter$ses = factor(inter$ses)
levels(inter$ses) =  c("low","middle", "high")
inter$religion = factor(inter$religion)
levels(inter$religion) = c("protestant", "catholic")
inter$gender = factor(inter$gender)
levels(inter$gender) = c("male","female")
inter$interfaith = factor(inter$interfaith)
levels(inter$interfaith) = c("yes", "no")
inter

Preparation

Uncounted the counts to get better sense of the counts in the data set

library(tidyr)
inter2 = inter %>% uncount(count)

Plots

Explanation

Socioeconomic Status - They intermarry in the middle class the highest. More males tend to intermarry than woman. Catholics tend to intermarry more than protesants

pi1 = ggplot(inter2)+
  aes(x=ses, fill=interfaith)+
  geom_bar(position = "fill")+
  theme_bw()+
  ggtitle("Socioeconomic Status in Relation with Intermarriages")+
  ylab("% of Data")+
  xlab("Socioeconomic Status")+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))+
  scale_x_discrete(labels = c("Low", "Middle","High"))


pi1

pi2 = ggplot(inter2)+
  aes(x=gender, fill=interfaith)+
  geom_bar(position = "fill")+
  theme_bw()+
  ggtitle("Gender in Relation with Intermarriages")+
  ylab("% of Data")+
  xlab("Gender")+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))+
